html_attributions: ฮ่องกง สถานีคนเดิน

reviews.text: Authentic hk zhi char. Went at about 2pm and there are still empty seats. Must order the salted egg prawn and the lala. Worth it only if you don’t need to queue for hours.

One star is for the restaurant decoration...  Food is below average and most dishes are salty compare to other places.  There are many decent restaurants nearby serving similar food and I would rather go there.
Price wise is ok but food quality just so so
Hong Kong traditional cuisine. Worth a try.

A local food place tucked away in ladies market on the 3rd floor of a building. I’ve been here twice the past 3 years and both times did not disappoint the one star knockoff is for the price and mediocre crab which they are known for. I would skip it and order other dishes. There is an English menu but it was difficult to order in English so I had to use my broken Cantonese haha. My favorite dish was the potato with beef and fried salty egg calamari/shrimp. I saw a lot of tables order the pork knuckles so I’ll try that next time. Environment is noisy and filled with locals and youngins hanging out with friends. Be prepared to wait 1hr + during dinner times. Overall I recommend this place if you’re ever hanging out around ladies market. Oh beer is drinked out of a bowl and make sure you clean the utensils with team and the big bowl they give you.
